Package ca.queensu.cs.cisc124.notes.interfaces

Interface Function1

  • All Known Implementing Classes:
    Linear, Square, TruncatedSquare
    public interface Function1
    An interface for real-valued, 1-dimensional functions of the form y = f(x).

    • Method Summary

      All Methods Instance Methods Abstract Methods Default Methods 
      Modifier and Type Method Description
      double eval​(double x)
      Evaluate the function at the specified argument returning y = f(x) if the function exists at x.
      default List<Double> eval​(List<Double> x)
      Evaluate the function at each of the arguments contained in the specified list returning a list containing the evaluated function values.

    • Method Detail

      • eval

        double eval​(double x)
        Evaluate the function at the specified argument returning y = f(x) if the function exists at x. Returns Double.NaN if the function does not exist at x.
        Parameters:
        x - the argument to the function
        Returns:
        the function evaluated at x

      • eval

        default List<Double> eval​(List<Double> x)
        Evaluate the function at each of the arguments contained in the specified list returning a list containing the evaluated function values. Double.NaN is used for each argument value where the function does not exist.
        Parameters:
        x - a list of arguments to the function
        Returns:
        a list of values of the function evaluated at each element of x
